## NumPy Boolean Comparison

NumPy boolean values (`np.True_`, `np.False_`) are not Python `True`/`False`. Use explicit comparison.

```python
# WRONG: Identity comparison fails
done = np.array([True])[0]
if done is True:  # False! np.True_ is not True
    ...

# RIGHT: Equality comparison or cast
if bool(done):
    ...
```

